lug":"bulk-forming-laxatives","fullItemName":"Bulk-forming laxatives"},{"id":"ba178fdc-1c2f-58e1-aec7-b1f903ed5207","slug":"cefalexin","fullItemName":"Cefalexin"},{"id":"524ca556-9a60-542a-9102-901470ef4882","slug":"co-amoxiclav","fullItemName":"Co-amoxiclav"},{"id":"463ca371-3542-5765-8350-4a0a640f0cae","slug":"ciprofloxacin","fullItemName":"Ciprofloxacin"},{"id":"231102c0-511c-5785-ac06-8720d28571cb","slug":"metronidazole","fullItemName":"Metronidazole"},{"id":"f2cde7d6-3b3a-5b9f-bf9c-9c7445a1ae6f","slug":"trimethoprim","fullItemName":"Trimethoprim"}]},{"id":"8b942243-eed9-557a-9678-01f6c77e2b91","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"7ccd6405-b8ec-557d-9d70-bce3f43accbd","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"544db73d-5bf7-5ac9-81f4-784210ec7343","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"f2fb4d8d-7ad7-55ef-837b-a9faa80ba34d","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"8cbe5c96-baf1-5b25-af5c-6f36a3d9ea3c","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"7518d3a3-e804-5074-908b-2b9f984cbf60","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"e84d6049-8652-59d8-a02d-c49972295f21","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"1de75d4a-a4c8-5742-add9-eabcb6711bcb","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"c90663d3-95e7-5f18-9718-27a43a51abbf","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"66636d9b-3ac8-5375-8f43-a29eb9de9f27","slug":"management-of-diverticulosis","fullItemName":"Management of diverticulosis","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d4e3aeaf-011a-4cac-938e-c882f1beb34f --><h3>How should I manage a person with diverticulosis?</h3><!-- end field d4e3aeaf-011a-4cac-938e-c882f1beb34f -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 9df230e6-e325-439e-a91a-cb23b0bcc1b5 --><!-- begin field 00a4beeb-44f9-4971-ad52-6d1267ad8ece --><p><strong>If a person has confirmed diverticulosis, provide the following advice:</strong></p><ul><li>If asymptomatic diverticulosis has been found incidentally while investigating other symptoms, no further investigations are needed.<ul><li>The gut and liver disease charity Guts UK (website available at <a href=\"https://gutscharity.org.uk/\" data-hyperlink-id=\"3d14b1cd-7c06-40ce-82cd-aa8700db28a0\">gutscharity.org.uk</a>) provides support for patients and families and has a patient information leaflet <a data-hyperlink-id=\"3d35ce92-ae27-41fe-b280-a98e004dc323\" href=\"https://gutscharity.org.uk/advice-and-information/information-leaflets/\" target=\"_blank\">Information about diverticular disease</a>.</li></ul></li><li>Recommend eating a healthy, balanced diet and having regular meals:<ul><li>The person's diet should contain whole grains, fruits, and vegetables.<ul><li>The Association of UK Dietitians has useful Food Fact Sheets on <a data-hyperlink-id=\"2d793581-0e77-4660-9f53-a98e004dc335\" href=\"https://www.bda.uk.com/foodfacts/fibrefoodfactsheet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Fibre</a> and <a data-hyperlink-id=\"9dcc8565-d54b-4949-b69c-a98e004dc3e3\" href=\"https://www.bda.uk.com/foodfacts/FruitVeg.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Fruit and vegetables - how to get five-a-day</a>.</li><li>The NHS has a useful patient information leaflet <a data-hyperlink-id=\"0aa0fabb-e06e-459f-b3e2-a98e004dc442\" href=\"https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/diverticular-disease-and-diverticulitis/\" target=\"_blank\">Diverticular disease and diverticulitis - prevention</a>.</li></ul></li><li>Fibre intake should be increased gradually (to minimize flatulence and bloating) — adults should aim to consume 30 g of fibre per day to reduce the risk of developing symptomatic <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diverticular-disease/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">diverticular disease</a>.<ul><li>Advise the person that the beneficial effects of increasing dietary fibre may take several weeks.</li><li>Advise that a high-fibre diet should be maintained for life.</li></ul></li><li>Public Health England's booklet <a data-hyperlink-id=\"4e907f8c-db7b-4721-a278-a98e004dc4b7\" href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/551502/Eatwell_Guide_booklet.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The Eatwell Guide</a> has patient information on eating a healthy, balanced diet.</li></ul></li><li>Recommend drinking an adequate fluid intake with a high-fibre diet, especially if there is a risk of dehydration.<ul><li>The Association of UK Dietitians has a useful Food Fact Sheet on <a data-hyperlink-id=\"b7fb7833-1382-42b7-9d8b-a98e004dc4f1\" href=\"https://www.bda.uk.com/foodfacts/fluid.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Fluid</a>.</li></ul></li><li>Routine follow-up is not necessary if there is no progression to symptomatic <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diverticular-disease/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">diverticular disease</a> or <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diverticular-disease/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">diverticulitis</a>.</li></ul><!-- end field 00a4beeb-44f9-4971-ad52-6d1267ad8ece --><!-- end item 9df230e6-e325-439e-a91a-cb23b0bcc1b5 -->","subChapters":[{"id":"ea94258b-2e90-5a83-a077-6ffb5c9d7bde","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-ba5","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field a86b34c8-4e01-40c6-8310-aa06e384f1be --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field a86b34c8-4e01-40c6-8310-aa06e384f1be -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item ba550d78-9a60-4181-bd0d-e987dc2e2f41 --><!-- begin field 848fd62d-03d8-4289-bec0-4a93773eb53d --><ul><li>The recommendations on the management of diverticulosis are based on expert opinion in the international consensus document <em>Management of patients with diverticulosis and diverticular disease</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diverticular-disease/references/\">Tursi, 2016</a>] and expert opinion in the Association of Coloproctology of Great Britain and Ireland (ACPGBI) <em>Commissioning guide: colonic diverticular disease</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diverticular-disease/references/\">ACPGBI, 2014</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 848fd62d-03d8-4289-bec0-4a93773eb53d --><!-- end item ba550d78-9a60-4181-bd0d-e987dc2e2f41 -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}